The paper discusses the relay selection problem in UAV communication networks, which involves optimizing factors such as network performance, distributed communication, and scalability. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper proposes the use of matching game theory to model the relay selection problem, which could fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The paper also discusses the challenges of relay selection in UAV networks, which could relate to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel classification of matching games, which could fall under the Game Theory (cs.GT) category.
